<chapter condition="TITLE=System Features: Biller Maintenance;ACCESS=BP" role="TOPIC">
  <title>Biller Maintenance</title>

  <section condition="TITLE=System Features: Biller Maintenance;PERM=audit_access;ACCESS=SY_BILLPB"
           id="BBM" role="TOPIC">
    <title>Overview</title>

    <para role="TEXT">As an administrator at a bank,you can add billing
    organisations which will be used as the payee under the Fund
    Transfer&gt;Bill Payment function. This will also include details on how
    to register the payee before creating the Bill Payment transactions. Bill
    Payment allows a customer user to pay their monthly bills online or other
    billing statement as long as they have the bill reference and the billing
    Organization exists.</para>
</section>
    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Biller Maintenance - Navigation</title>

      <para role="TEXT">To navigate to the <emphasis role="bold">Biller
      Maintenance</emphasis> function, from the toolbar, select
      <emphasis>System Features</emphasis> from the home page, then select
      <emphasis>Biller Maintenance</emphasis> from the left navigation
      menu.</para>
    </section>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Biller Maintenance Options</title>

      <para role="TEXT">The Biller Maintenance options that are part of the
      left menu are listed in the following:</para>

      <variablelist role="TEXT">
        <varlistentry>
          <term><guimenuitem moreinfo="none">Bill
          Payment</guimenuitem>:</term>

          <listitem>
            <para>Maintain billing organisation details for customers to
            request payment of specific bills.</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
    </section>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Biller Maintenance - Bill Payment</title>

      <para role="TEXT">This option is used by the Bank Administrator to
      Maintain Billers details for customers. When you select this option, you
      are presented with a list of all the existing Biller accounts at your
      bank. You can search the list by entering search criteria in the
      <guilabel moreinfo="none">Biller Code</guilabel>, <guilabel
      moreinfo="none">Payee Name, </guilabel><guilabel
      moreinfo="none">Category</guilabel>, <guilabel
      moreinfo="none">Status</guilabel> and <guilabel>Actor</guilabel> fields
      at the top of the page.</para>

      <note>
        <para>The <guilabel>Status</guilabel> and <guilabel>Actor</guilabel>
        fields are available if maker-checker functionality is enabled.</para>
      </note>

      <para role="TEXT">The list of existing Billers has the following
      columns:</para>

